Third-party components are NOT covered by the licence above and are not
distributed in this repository. `tools/build-vendor.mjs` fetches them from npm
at build time:

  JASSUB (ASS subtitle rendering, embeds libass)
      LGPL-2.1-or-later AND (FTL OR GPL-2.0-or-later) AND MIT
      AND MIT-Modern-Variant AND ISC AND NTP AND Zlib AND BSL-1.0
      https://github.com/ThaUnknown/jassub

  libpgs (PGS subtitle rendering)
      MIT
      https://github.com/Arcus92/libpgs-js

Both are loaded as separate bundles through their published interfaces, so
this repository stays MIT. See README.md for how that constrains the E-AC3
work, which cannot use a GPL decoder without relicensing the whole project.
